flowchart LR
    %% GOAL: Orchestrate agents to update the agent guidance system through a context engineering process.
    %% PROFILE: Orchestration-Context-Engineer
    %% OUTPUT: Completed plans and audit reports in docs/plans/completed/
    %% GUIDELINE: Strict NO CODE policy - context engineering for guidance only.
    %% GUIDELINE: Every execution issue or audit failure MUST trigger a return to the planning stage.
    %% GUIDELINE: assets/guidelines/orchestration-policy.yml - Agent spawning rules, escalation, status management
    %% GUIDELINE: assets/guidelines/user-story-testing.yml - User simulator testing patterns
    %% INPUT_PATH: agents/orchestration/orchestration-guidance/inputs.yml

    Start((Start)) --> LoadInputs[Load Context Inputs]

    %% Input Verification & Search Logic: Ensure we have all necessary context from inputs.yml
    LoadInputs --> ReviewInputs[Review All Listed Inputs]
    ReviewInputs --> CheckInputs{All Inputs Found?}

    %% If inputs are missing, attempt to self-heal by searching
    CheckInputs -- "No: Missing" --> SearchInputs[Search for Missing Inputs]
    SearchInputs --> Found{Found?}

    %% If found elsewhere, update paths to maintain continuity
    Found -- "Yes: Update paths" --> UpdateRefs[Update References & Flag]
    UpdateRefs --> ReviewInputs

    %% Critical failure: Stop and ask user if context cannot be resolved
    Found -- "No: Stop" --> AskUser((Ask User for Clarification))

    %% Proceed only when context is fully loaded and verified
    CheckInputs -- "Yes: Verified" --> SpawnDeployWorktree[Spawn deploy-worktree Agent]

    %% Isolate work and initialize the planning environment
    %% deploy-worktree agent handles worktree setup and verification per its internal criteria
    SpawnDeployWorktree --> WorktreeValid{Worktree Valid?}
    WorktreeValid -- "No: Failed verification" --> AskUser

    %% ========================================
    %% PLANNING & REVIEW SUBGRAPH
    %% ========================================
    %% Both implementation and test plans must be approved before execution begins.
    %% This ensures guidance quality is validated BEFORE implementation.
    %%
    %% FEEDBACK LOOP ENTRY POINTS:
    %% This phase receives feedback from three downstream validation points:
    %% 1. Implementation Issues (line 113): Execution-time problems → Update plan and re-plan
    %% 2. Walkthrough Failures (line 146): Guidance gaps from test-guidance-simulator → Re-execute both loops
    %% 3. Final Audit Failures (line 139): Output quality issues → Update plan and re-plan
    %%
    %% When re-entering from walkthrough failures:
    %% - planner-teach receives structured friction report with specific gap details
    %% - Both Implementation Planning Loop and Test-Guidance Planning Loop re-run
    %% - This ensures guidance fixes don't create inconsistencies between implementation and test plans

    WorktreeValid -- "Yes: Verified" --> PlanningReview[Enter Planning & Review Phase]

    subgraph Planning ["Planning & Review Subgraph"]
        %% ----------------------------------------
        %% LOOP 1: IMPLEMENTATION PLANNING LOOP
        %% ----------------------------------------
        %% LOOP_DEFINITION: assets/definitions/agent-loops.yml#planner-loop
        %% MAX_ITERATIONS: 5 (per planner-loop definition)
        %% ESCALATION: If max iterations reached without approval, stop and Ask User with iteration context
        %%
        %% WALKTHROUGH FEEDBACK HANDLING:
        %% When returning from Guidance Validation Phase with walkthrough failures:
        %% - planner-teach receives friction report from test-guidance-simulator
        %% - Friction points categorized as CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW
        %% - planner-teach updates guidance to address gaps (paths, fences, signposts)
        %% - Plan must be re-approved by planner-reviewer before proceeding
        %% - Specific gap types trigger specific teacher agents via planner-teach coordination
        PlanningReview --> ImplPlanningLoop{Implementation Planning Loop}

        ImplPlanningLoop --> SpawnPlannerTeach[Spawn planner-teach Agent]
        SpawnPlannerTeach --> SpawnImplReviewer[Spawn planner-reviewer Agent]

        %% Quality Gate: Reviewer must approve the implementation plan
        SpawnImplReviewer --> ImplApproved{Implementation Plan Approved?}

        %% Iterative refinement: Reuse planner-teach to address reviewer feedback
        ImplApproved -- "No: Refine" --> SpawnPlannerTeachFix[Spawn planner-teach Agent]
        SpawnPlannerTeachFix --> SpawnImplReviewer

        %% ----------------------------------------
        %% LOOP 2: TEST-GUIDANCE PLANNING LOOP
        %% ----------------------------------------
        %% This loop runs AFTER implementation planning is approved
        %% Plans the guidance-blind-test validation strategy
        %% GUIDELINE: assets/definitions/strategy-guidance-blind-test.yml
        %% GUIDELINE: assets/definitions/guidance-test-scenarios.yml
        ImplApproved -- "Yes: Ready" --> TestPlanningLoop{Test-Guidance Planning Loop}

        TestPlanningLoop --> SpawnTestPlanner[Spawn planner-test-guidance Agent]
        SpawnTestPlanner --> SpawnTestReviewer[Spawn planner-reviewer Agent]

        %% Quality Gate: Reviewer must approve the test-guidance plan
        SpawnTestReviewer --> TestPlanApproved{Test Plan Approved?}

        %% Iterative refinement for test plan
        TestPlanApproved -- "No: Refine" --> SpawnTestPlannerFix[Spawn planner-test-guidance Agent]
        SpawnTestPlannerFix --> SpawnTestReviewer

        %% Check for test planning failures that require returning to implementation planning
        TestPlanApproved -- "Yes: Check Viability" --> TestPlanViable{Test Plan Viable?}

        %% If test plan reveals implementation plan issues, return to teaching
        TestPlanViable -- "No: Implementation Issues Found" --> UpdateImplPlan[Update Implementation Plan]
        UpdateImplPlan -.->|Return to Loop 1| ImplPlanningLoop
    end

    %% NOTE: Test Plan (from Loop 2) drives guidance-test-loop execution later in Guidance Validation Phase
    %% The approved test plan defines which walkthrough scenarios test-guidance-simulator will execute

    %% ========================================
    %% EXECUTION PHASE: Implement Guidance Changes
    %% ========================================
    %% Execution begins ONLY after both plans are approved:
    %% - Implementation plan approved (planner-teach)
    %% - Test plan approved (planner-test-guidance)
    TestPlanViable -- "Yes: Both Plans Ready" --> SpawnTeachers[Spawn teacher agents]
    SpawnTeachers --> ExecutePhases[Execute Implementation Phases]

    %% Continuous monitoring for execution-time issues
    ExecutePhases --> ImplIssues{Implementation Issues?}

    %% Fail-Fast & Recover: Return to Planning & Review phase on any execution issues
    ImplIssues -- "Yes: Failed" --> OffloadIssues[Offload to Appropriate Agent]
    OffloadIssues --> UpdatePlan[Update Live Plan]
    UpdatePlan -.->|Return to Planning & Review| PlanningReview

    %% ========================================
    %% GUIDANCE VALIDATION PHASE
    %% ========================================
    %% Execute the test-guidance plan created in Planning Loop 2
    %% Uses guidance-blind-test strategy to validate guidance completeness
    %% GUIDELINE: assets/definitions/strategy-guidance-blind-test.yml
    %% LOOP_DEFINITION: assets/definitions/agent-loops.yml#guidance-test-loop
    %% MAX_ITERATIONS: 3 (per guidance-test-loop definition)
    %% ESCALATION: If max iterations reached without passing validation, stop and Ask User with gap context
    ImplIssues -- "No: Done" --> ExecuteGuidanceTests[Execute Test-Guidance Phases]
    ExecuteGuidanceTests --> SpawnGuidanceSim[Spawn test-guidance-simulator]
    %% PLAN STATUS UPDATE: Consume test results and update plan task statuses
    %% Reference: assets/guidelines/orchestration-policy.yml - Plan Status Management rule
    %% This step ensures task statuses reflect test outcomes before evaluating overall guidance validity
    SpawnGuidanceSim --> UpdateTestStatuses[Update Plan Task Statuses from Test Results]
    UpdateTestStatuses --> GuidancePassed{Guidance Valid?}

    %% ========================================
    %% GUIDANCE REPAIR LOOP: Failing walkthrough tests trigger return to Planning-Teach Loop
    %% ========================================
    %% BEHAVIOR: When test-guidance-simulator reports friction points:
    %% 1. Categorize gaps by severity (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW from test-guidance-simulator)
    %% 2. Route to appropriate teacher agent based on gap type:
    %% - Process/step clarity issues → Return to Implementation Planning Loop (planner-teach)
    %% - Reference/path issues → Return to Implementation Planning Loop (planner-teach)
    %% - Test scenario design issues → Return to Test-Guidance Planning Loop (planner-test-guidance)
    %% 3. Teacher agents (via planner-teach) receive:
    %% - Structured friction report from test-guidance-simulator
    %% - Specific guidance gaps with suggested fixes
    %% - Context on which walkthrough scenarios failed
    %% 4. Re-execute BOTH planning loops to ensure consistency after fixes
    %% 5. Track iteration count against guidance-test-loop max_iterations (3)
    %% ========================================
    GuidancePassed -- "No: Gaps Found" --> CategorizeGaps[Categorize Friction Points & Route to Teacher Agents]
    CategorizeGaps --> UpdatePlanGaps[Update Plan with Walkthrough Failure Details]
    UpdatePlanGaps -.->|Return to Planning & Review: Re-execute Both Loops| PlanningReview

    %% ========================================
    %% FINAL AUDIT PHASE
    %% ========================================
    GuidancePassed -- "Yes: Verified" --> SpawnAudit[Spawn test-final-output Audit]
    SpawnAudit --> FinalAudit{Final Audit Passed?}

    %% If audit fails, loop back to Planning & Review phase for correction
    FinalAudit -- "No: Failed" --> UpdatePlanIssues[Update Plan with Audit Issues]
    UpdatePlanIssues -.->|Return to Planning & Review| PlanningReview

    %% ========================================
    %% FINALIZATION
    %% ========================================
    %% Success: All criteria met. Finalize the work.
    FinalAudit -- "Yes: Verified" --> MoveCompleted[Copy Completed Work to docs/plans/completed/]
    MoveCompleted --> End((End))

    %% COPY planning folder to completed/ (not move) - live/ may continue with follow-on work
    %% Only user moves completed/ folders to archived/ subdirectory

    %% Styling for feedback loops (return paths to Planning & Review)
    %% These dotted lines represent quality improvement cycles
    classDef dashedstroke stroke-dasharray: 5 5;
    linkStyle 23,27,31 stroke:#888,stroke-width:2px,stroke-dasharray: 5 5;
